8 POLICY COMMITTEE RECOMMENDATION
9 An Act relating to the Department of Environmental
Quality; requiring the promulgation of rules
10 establishing water quality criteria for aluminum;
listing criteria for promulgated rules; authorizing
11 adoption or incorporation by reference of certain
criteria; requiring criteria be applied to certain
12 permitting; listing requirements for application to
permits; requiring criteria be included in certain
13 triennial review; authorizing updates to criteria;
providing for codification; and providing an
14 effective date.
15
16
17
18 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
19 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
20 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 2-6-112 of Title 27A, unless
21 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
22 A. By December 31, 2028, the Department of Environmental
23 Quality shall promulgate rules that establish numeric water quality
24
Req. No. 16355 Page 1

1 crit eria for aluminum applicable to surface waters of the State of
2 Oklahoma. The criteria shall:
3 1. Be developed in accordance with Section 303(c) of the
4 federal Clean Water Act and its implementing regulations;
5 2. Be consistent with current U.S. Environmental Protection
6 Agency (EPA) guidance, including use of any recommended hardness-
7 based or water-chemistry-based criteria equations, bioavailability
8 models, or site-specific adjustment procedures; and
9 3. Incorporate site-specific conditions, where scientifically
10 appropriate, including water hardness, pH, dissolved organic carbon,
11 or other parameters affecting aluminum toxicity.
12 The Department may adopt or incorporate by reference any EPA
13 criteria, guidance documents, or calculation tools necessary to
14 implement the provisions of this section.
15 B. Following promulgation of the rules required in subsection
16 A, the Department shall apply the numeric aluminum water quality
17 criteria in all Oklahoma Pollutant Discharge Elimination System
18 (OPDES) permits where aluminum may be discharged. The Department
19 shall, consistent with federal and state law:
20 1. Require permittees to conduct monitoring and reporting of
21 aluminum and related parameters necessary to evaluate compliance
22 with water-quality-based standards;
23 2. Establish water-quality-based effluent limits where needed
24 to ensure compliance with the numeric criteria;
Req. No. 16355 Page 2

1 3. Consider site-specific conditions, mixing zones, dilution
2 allowances, and receiving-water characteristics in calculating any
3 water-quality-based effluent limits; and
4 4. Include any additional monitoring, best management
5 practices, or adaptive management conditions necessary to assure
6 protection of water quality.
7 C. The Department shall include the aluminum criteria in each
8 triennial review of Oklahoma Water Quality Standards required under
9 Section 303(c) of the Clean Water Act. The Department shall revise
10 such criteria as needed to reflect new science, updated EPA
11 recommendations, or site-specific data, and shall submit any
12 revisions to the U.S. Environmental Protection Agency for approval.
13 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
